===Etymology===
Anglo-Norman ''[[gotere]]'', from Old French ''[[gotiere]]'' (French ''[[gouttière]]''), ultimately from Latin ''[[gutta]]'' ‘drop’.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/'gʌtə/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# a [[ditch]] along the side of a [[road]]
# a [[duct]] or [[channel]] beneath the [[eave]]s of a [[building]] to carry [[rain]] [[water]]
# [[groove]]s down the [[side]]s of a [[bowling]] [[lane]]
# a space between printed columns of text
# (British) a [[drainage]] [[channel]]

